Subject: Re: starter troubleshooting

On Mon, 19 May 2003, Don J wrote:

>Now I'm thinking maybe starter bushing is toasted, or incorrect?

Possibly.  If the bushing is worn oversize, it might allow enough slop
to keep the starter gear from engaging the flywheel.

>Is it true there is absolutely no way a 6v flywheel will work with a 12v
>starter?

I punched "starter bushing" into the archives
( http://www.type2.com/archive/search-vintagebus.html ) and got the
following good hits:

http://www.type2.com/archive/vintagebus/011633.html
http://www.type2.com/archive/vintagebus/037197.html
http://www.type2.com/archive/vintagebus/008519.html
http://www.type2.com/archive/vintagebus/048100.html

>One other curious thing, when I accidentally touched big pole on
>solenoid to starter body, it shot serious sparks, and actually made
>a burn mark on the starter.

Uh, yeah.  That's because you basically shorted directly across the
battery, from the positive terminal to ground.  It's a good way to
melt screwdrivers and cook batteries.  So don't do that.

Matt Roberds
